<h2>Zephyrhills AC repair — serving the old town, the new communities, and everything between</h2>
<p>Zephyrhills is a study in contrasts, and when homeowners search for <a href="/services/ac-repair-tampa/">AC repair in Zephyrhills</a>, they're almost always calling from one of three very different housing situations. The original <strong>Zephyrhills core</strong> around 5th Avenue has housing stock dating to the 1950s and 1960s, with older package units, wall-mount systems, and aging ductwork that requires careful hands-on diagnosis. <strong>Betmar Acres</strong> and other manufactured home communities along Gall Boulevard represent one of the largest concentrations of platform AC and flex duct systems in east Pasco. And the eastern growth corridor — <strong>Silverado</strong>, <strong>Abbott Park</strong>, <strong>Link's Landing</strong>, <strong>Hidden River</strong> — has added thousands of builder-grade systems since 2015 that are now reaching their first major service calls.</p>

<p>Our Wesley Chapel base puts us about 20–30 minutes from downtown Zephyrhills via Highway 54 or SR-56. We run this route daily and know the community well — the neighborhoods, the common equipment brands, and the specific failure modes each area sees most often. All Zephyrhills ZIP codes (33540, 33541, 33542) are within our standard same-day service window when route availability allows.</p>

<h2>The 10 most common AC repairs we do in Zephyrhills homes</h2>
<p>Across all Zephyrhills neighborhoods these failure modes account for roughly 85% of the service calls we run — in rough order of frequency with honest 2026 pricing:</p>
<ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3 text-slate-700 mt-4">
  <li><strong>Failed run capacitor</strong> — outdoor unit hums but won't start. The #1 service call in Zephyrhills in any given July. <strong>$180–$320.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Burned-out contactor</strong> — welded-shut (dangerous, compressor damage risk) or failure-open. <strong>$180–$350.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Manufactured home flex duct disconnection</strong> — under-floor duct boots disconnect from registers due to vibration or rodent activity. Can drop 30% of cooling capacity; diagnosis and repair is a specialty. <strong>$180–$450 depending on access.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Clogged condensate drain / failed float switch</strong> — east Pasco humidity clogs drain lines and trips safety switches. <strong>$150–$275.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Frozen evaporator coil</strong> — ice on the copper line, weak supply air. Dirty filter, failing blower, or low refrigerant. Shut off, thaw 2 hours, call. <strong>$250–$850.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>R-22 refrigerant leak on Colony Hills / 5th Ave older equipment</strong> — R-22 was phased out in 2020; leaks on remaining systems are usually a replace-vs-repair conversation. <strong>$450–$1,200 if repair makes sense; otherwise $7,500+ replacement.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Silverado / Abbott Park builder-grade return-air deficiency</strong> — two-story floor plans with undersized returns. Fix is adding a return, not upsizing the unit. <strong>$450–$1,200.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Platform compressor failure (manufactured homes)</strong> — Nordyne and Intertherm platform systems are serviceable but parts are more specialized. <strong>$1,200–$2,400.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Thermostat / control board (post-storm surge)</strong> — common east of Skydive City where utility power quality runs noticeably worse than metro Tampa. <strong>$200–$600.</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Compressor failure on 15+ year old equipment</strong> — on systems this age, replacement is usually the right call. <strong>Out of warranty: $2,200–$3,800; usually tips to replacement instead.</strong></li>
</ol>

<h2>Manufactured home HVAC — what Betmar Acres and similar Zephyrhills communities need</h2>
<p>Manufactured home HVAC is a specialty, not a side service for us. These homes typically use <strong>platform-mount AC systems</strong> installed in a dedicated HVAC closet or under the home, with flexible ductwork running through the floor system. Common brands include Nordyne, Goodman, and older Intertherm units. The failure modes are different from stick-built homes:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Flex duct disconnections under the floor</strong> — vibration and rodent activity disconnect duct boots from floor registers, causing 20–30% cooling losses. We inspect the full duct run, not just the unit, on every service call.</li>
  <li><strong>Platform system capacitor and compressor failures</strong> — common parts we carry for Nordyne, Goodman, and Intertherm platform systems. Capacitor replacement on these is a one-trip repair.</li>
  <li><strong>Low return-air capacity</strong> — many older manufactured homes have a single return-air grille that's undersized for the system, causing the unit to starve for airflow and short-cycle. We can add additional returns to solve comfort complaints without equipment replacement.</li>
  <li><strong>Roof-mount package unit service</strong> — some Zephyrhills manufactured homes have rooftop package units. Service includes access ladder work and coil cleaning from the roof deck. We're set up for it.</li>
</ul>

